data.description:
Welcome to this beautiful 3-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home conveniently located in central Fife neighborhood. Situated on a quiet cul de sac, this house offers a serene and peaceful environment. The open floor plan and abundance of natural sunlight create a warm and inviting atmosphere throughout. The fully fenced backyard provides privacy and security, perfect for outdoor activities and entertaining. Additionally, a storage shed offers ample space for all your storage needs. Enjoy cozy evenings by the gas fireplace, adding a touch of elegance to the living area. The kitchen boasts matching appliances, including a microwave, and features laminate flooring for easy maintenance. Blinds throughout the house ensure privacy and shade when needed. The convenience of a washer and dryer (this appliance is 'as-is') is included for your convenience. With a 2-car tandem garage, parking is never a hassle. This home is ideally located close to schools, parks, shopping, and restaurants, making it a perfect choice for those seeking convenience and accessibility. Commuting is a breeze with easy access to freeways and public transportation nearby. No smoking. No pets.

RENTAL TERMS:
Rent: $2880.00
Available: 1/18/2024
Application Fee: $50
Security Deposit: $ 2880.00
Utilities: Tenant responsibility
Renters Insurance Required: $11.50/month tenant liability insurance or supply own
Non-Refundable Admin Fee: $75
Resident Benefit Pkg: $25/month
Lease Terms: 12+ months

SPECIAL NOTES:
Applicants are to verify all material facts, including but not limited to room sizes, utilities, schools, HOA rules, community amenities, fees, and costs.
The applicant must verify if the unit is approved for HUD housing vouchers.
The applicant is to verify the required Rental Income. This could vary if the property is within the limits of the City of Tacoma.

MOVE-IN COSTS: A Holding Fee equal to 25% of the security deposit will be required to take the property off the market. This is due within 24 hours after approval and will be applied to your security deposit at lease signing. The base Security deposit is equal to one month's rent and can be more if approved with a pet and/or an Adverse approval.

Upon Move-in one months rent/charges will be due and any pro-rated charges will be applied for the second month.

RENTAL CRITERIA: Please visit our website for our detailed rental criteria. We DO NOT answer screening criteria qualification questions over the phone.

RESIDENT BENEFIT PACKAGE: All Steady Property Management residents are enrolled in the Resident Benefits Package (RBP) for $25/month which includes HVAC air filter delivery (for applicable properties), credit building to help boost your credit score with timely rent payments, $1M Identity Protection, utility concierge service making utility connection a breeze during your move-in, our best-in-class resident rewards program, 24/7 maintenance, FREE ACH payment, online portal, One-time late fee waived if paid by the 10th and much more! More details upon application. ALL Tenants are enrolled in the RBP.

APPLICATION POLICIES AND PROCEDURES

VISIT THE PROPERTY: YOU ARE REQUIRED TO VIEW THE PROPERTY PRIOR TO APPLYING. We require all showing appts to be Pre-Qualified by answering a few questions and submitting a current Drivers License, or Government-issued ID.

POINT SYSTEM: Applications are processed on a point system and scored based upon factors including, but not limited to rental history, income, employment eviction history, and credit score. If your application does not meet our minimum qualifications, an additional security deposit may be required.

MULTIPLE APPLICATIONS: In the case where we receive more than one application on a property, we will process ALL applications and approve the highest-scored applicant. If your application is approved with fewer points, we do hold applications open for 60 days. You may apply your pre-approved application towards any of our other properties within those 60 days WITHOUT having to pay an application fee again, HOWEVER, we will need to be able to re-verify income.

EVERY APPLICANT MUST FILL OUT AN ANIMAL APPLICATION: Whether you are applying with or without a pet, you MUST fill out the pet application found in the link below. Just copy and paste the link into your browser and follow the prompts. YOUR APPLICATION WILL NOT BE CONSIDERED COMPLETE WITHOUT THIS FILLED OUT. The cost is $20 for the first pet, and $15 for each pet thereafter. There is $0 cost for service animals or no pets. https
steadypm.petscreening.com/ .

DELAYED APPLICATION: Steady Property Management cannot be held responsible if your application is delayed or denied because our inquiries to verify information from outside sources is delayed, denied or ignored.

APPLICATION TIME FRAME: Applications are processed in 1-3 business days. The time required varies based on the responsiveness of your landlords and employers and other business demands. Steady PM uses a third party to process all applications.

IF APPROVED: Please note, if approved, Steady Property Management will require the reservation fee to be paid by within 24 hours.

** By inquiring about this property, you are consenting to receive emails and/or text messages from Steady Property Management. **

Steady Property Management has made every effort to accurately represent the property in all marketing and communications. The property will be in rent-ready condition including a thorough cleaning and everything should be in good working order. This does not mean it will be perfect. The property is accepted by you in its current cosmetic condition no further cosmetic alterations will be made. You will have signed a binding lease before moving in. If for ANY reason you decide not to accept the property you will be held legally responsible for the term of the lease according to WA statues. Applicant/Tenant agrees to accept the property "AS IS". Provided the property meets normal and ordinary standards of safety, health, and livability.

Steady Property Management does business in accordance with the Federal, State and Local Fair Housing laws and welcomes Persons of all Race, Color, Disability, Religious Creed, Ancestry, Sex, Familial Status, Sexual Preference, Gender Identity, Age and National Origin. We process applications and score is on the criteria described in this policy. We select the best-qualified tenant based on the highest scoring application. We do not accept comprehensive reusable tenant screening reports

Amenities: Fully fenced backyard, Storage shed, back patio, Gas fireplace, HOA, Cul de Sac, quiet neighborhood, close to schools and parks, natural sunlight, Open floor plan, 2 story, microwave, matching appliances, Blinds throughout, washer/dryer, Laminate flooring thoughout, carpet, hardwoods throughout, 2 car garage, close to shopping and restaurants, Close to freeways, public transportation nearby
